Governor of Kaduna State, Mallam Nasir El-Rufai, is expected to tee off the first ever Pro-Am Golf Tournament at the Armed Forces Staff College in Jaji, near Kaduna, in its over 50 years in existence. The event, which started on February 1, will see some 150 professional golfers and 350 amateurs fight for honours at the Ola Saad Ibrahim Golf Club situated inside the vast complex of the College.   Troost-Ekong doubtful for Burnley     Makinde names Lawal   Shooting Star’s GM     TIT BITS FROM CAMEROON   An elated Commandant of the Infantry Corps of the Nigeria Army, Major General V. O. Ezugwu said that he was pleased with the hosting of the Pro-Am since the event would expose the Jaji Club to a larger golfing community in Nigeria. Ezugwu equally mentioned that hosting over 500 golfers from across Nigeria would surely indicate the amount of peace the Armed Forces have restored in Kaduna State